<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-265-936  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 265 936.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  March 19 1990 v12 n12 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A/UX 2.0 gives Unix Mac interface, lets users run multipleapplications. (Apple Computer Inc. upgrades operating system)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lach, Eric; Marshall, Martin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple Computer Inc announces the midyear availability of A/UX 2.0.andO;The upgraded operating system will provide the full functionalityof the Macintosh graphical user interface in a Unix environment.andO;Users will have the capability of operating Macintosh, Unix and XWindow System applications concurrently on separate windows.andP;  AnyMacintosh applications in 32-bit mode will operate over the newsystem.andP;  The system is designed, with its Commando feature, toassist novice programmers in constructing command lines throughthe insertion of dialog boxes that display the availableprogramming options.andP;  The upgraded system supports standard Unixcomponents and gives full implementation to AT and T's Unix System5 2.2 with BSD 4.3 extensions.andP;  Users who purchase the A/UX 1.1system on or after March 19, 1990, will receive A/UX 2.0 free assoon as the system is shipped.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   A/UX 2.0 (Operating system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionUNIX-Like Operating SystemsGraphical User Interface.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>